        'apps.oemLinks.iir.pub.summaryLabel': 'Main contents',
        'apps.oemLinks.iir.pub.summary': '<li>HTHPs (heat above 80°C) for industrial decarbonisation: ~37% of global energy use is industrial heating; 100–200°C is a core target band for food, chemical, textile, paper, and plastics processes.</li><li>Three routes—vapor-compression, absorption, and hybrid absorption–compression—with simultaneous heating/cooling and thermal-storage integration.</li><li>Working fluids, compressors, commercial products (about 90–300°C, kW to 100 MW), case studies, and COP &gt;1.5 vs boilers; economics tied to electricity–fuel price ratios and grid carbon intensity.</li><li>Policy levers: performance-based subsidies, demonstrations, carbon pricing, workforce training, and clarity on refrigerant phase-out timelines; includes a two-page Summary for Policymakers.</li>',
