        'apps.oemLinks.bsria.pub.title': 'Worldwide Heat Pump Markets 2026 — with World Domestic & Commercial Boilers Market 2026',
        'apps.oemLinks.bsria.pub.meta': 'BSRIA Market Intelligence · primary research late 2025–Q1 2026 · ~3.8 boilers sold per hydronic heat pump in 2025',
        'apps.oemLinks.bsria.pub.summaryLabel': 'Main findings (global)',
        'apps.oemLinks.bsria.pub.summary': '<li>2025 sales: ~3.5 million hydronic heat pumps (+4% after a weak 2024); just under 13 million boilers sold (~90% gas). Boiler market broadly flat; transition remains gradual.</li><li>Ratio 3.8 boilers per hydronic heat pump in 2025; ~200 million boilers in operation worldwide (~half older non-condensing units).</li><li>~73% of global heating demand is replacement/retrofit (&gt;90% in mature markets)—the main competitive arena for boilers, heat pumps, hybrids, and district heating.</li><li>Forecasts: hydronic heat pumps +8% CAGR (2019–2029); fossil fuel boilers −2% CAGR (2019–2029). By 2029, hydronic heat pumps ~12% of replacement/retrofit activity. Progressive 2035 EU scenario: ~+20% heat pump growth vs ~−7% gas boilers in top five European heating markets.</li>',
